SIMPLE: explosion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Explosion
<hw>Ex*plo"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>explosio</ets> a driving off by clapping: cf. F.
<ets>explosion</ets> explosion. See <er>Explode</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of exploding; detonation; a chemical action which causes
the sudden formation of a great volume of expanded gas; <as>as, the
<ex>explosion</ex> of gunpowder, of fire damp, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bursting with violence and loud noise, because of
internal pressure; <as>as, the <ex>explosion</ex> of a gun, a bomb, a
steam boiler, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A violent outburst of feeling, manifested by excited
language, action, etc.; <as>as, an <ex>explosion</ex> of
wrath</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A formidable <qex>explosion</qex> of high-church fanaticism.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>a sudden and substantial increase; a rapid
acceleration; <as>as, the population <ex>explosion</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Explosive</ent>⟦br⟧
